File: Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula said a decision on e-tolls could be made public before Christmas. JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says the nation will be informed soon on the future of e-tolls. Mbalula was speaking on the sidelines of the festive road safety operations launch in Johannesburg. READ: No decision on e-tolls yet He said a decision could be made public before Christmas. "The matter is before Cabinet," he said. He said once a decision has been finalised, the public will be informed. READ: 'We will never pay e-tolls', says Gauteng motorists In November, the minister said government is considering alternatives to dealing with Gauteng e-tolls. Mbalula said e-tolls won't be implemented in terms of the current scheme.